  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Mixed economic data shows manufacturing strengthening (Philly Fed index 26.7 vs 12.0 expected) while services remain weak, with accelerating input price pressures across both sectors suggesting persistent inflation. Geopolitical tensions around Iran create binary outcomes for energy/inflation while Fed's Williams acknowledges crosscurrents and uncertainty around tariff impacts and potential supply shocks.",
    "regimeImpact": "Relief rally thesis intact as stocks hit records on Middle East truce hopes, but rising input costs and geopolitical binary risks support maintaining defensive positioning.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder as BTC remains below $75,000 structural resistance despite approaching that level",
      "Monitor oil prices closely as Iran tensions create stagflation risk if crude breaks above $100",
      "Keep Maturity sector overweight given mixed economic data and Fed uncertainty ahead of April 2 tariff deadline"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Philadelphia Fed manufacturing index surge to 26.7 (vs 12.0 expected) signals economic resilience but with concerning price pressures.",
      "Services prices paid index jumped to 73.8 from 62.5, showing broad-based input cost inflation acceleration.",
      "Initial claims dropped to 207,000 but continuing claims rose 31,000, reflecting labor market crosscurrents Williams highlighted.",
      "Bitcoin approaching $75,000 resistance while geopolitical uncertainty creates binary risk/reward setup for crypto markets."
    ]
